name: hive-thrift-py
raw_recipe:
{%set name = "hive-thrift-py" %}
{%set version = "0.0.1" %}
{%set hash_type = "sha256" %}
{%set hash_val = "c0b2554527beb040c8009b7af9f363f0498df2f985746c8dfd6cc41fdce3d6e1" %}

package:
  name: {{ name }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  {{ hash_type }}: {{ hash_val }}
  patches:
    - setup.patch  # [win]

build:
  number: 0
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record=record.txt

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools

  run:
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - fb303
    - fb303_scripts
    - hive_metastore
    - hive_serde
    - hive_service
    - queryplan
    - thrift
    - thrift.protocol
    - thrift.reflection
    - thrift.reflection.limited
    - thrift.server
    - thrift.transport

about:
  home: http://hive.apache.org
  license: Apache 2.0
  summary: 'Hive Python Thrift Libs'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - pmlandwehr
